1
00:00:47,840 --> 00:00:49,520
The preliminary results just came out yesterday.

2
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:50,920
The semi-finals are today.

3
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:52,200
This is so exciting.

4
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:54,200
My first time on stage was awesome.

5
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:54,880
I feel like I'm not

6
00:00:54,880 --> 00:00:56,120
the old Sai Meng anymore.

7
00:00:56,120 --> 00:00:57,280
I'm Brother Meng.

8
00:00:57,880 --> 00:00:59,040
Let's go to the venue now.

9
00:00:59,040 --> 00:01:00,840
We can rehearse a few more times.

10
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:03,360
What's wrong, bro?

11
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:04,760
Too excited to unlock it?

12
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:28,280
Damn it.

13
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:30,120
What kind of moron did this?

14
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:30,980
My instrument!

15
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:45,160
We're doomed.

16
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:49,450
Who holds such a grudge against us?

17
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:53,860
Could it be that Jiang guy you mentioned?

18
00:01:57,520 --> 00:01:58,200
Come back.

19
00:01:58,880 --> 00:02:00,210
Why are you stopping me?

20
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:01,640
He's a dirty scumbag.

21
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:02,880
I'm gonna go mess him up.

22
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:03,920
We have no proof.

23
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:06,050
He won't admit to it.

24
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:07,280
Then what do we do?

25
00:02:07,960 --> 00:02:08,840
The competition is tonight,

26
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:10,570
and we don't have instruments.

27
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:17,400
I need some air.

28
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:24,320
Call the police first.

29
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:25,200
Hurry.

30
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:26,660
I'll clean this up.

31
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:44,240
How are you doing?

32
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:45,960
You just gave them 20,000.

33
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:47,490
They've backed off for now.

34
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:52,120
Don't fight them hard. Wait for my word.

35
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:54,250
Are you in some kind of trouble?

36
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:56,360
Liu Ma.

37
00:02:57,160 --> 00:02:58,690
After a long run of bad luck,

38
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:00,240
things will turn around.

39
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:18,960
Here, play with this for a while.

40
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,600
Hurry up.

41
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:55,480
Let's leave Lincang

42
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:56,810
with an unplugged song.

43
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:00,600
The competition didn't say

44
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:01,880
we have to use drums, bass,

45
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:03,080
or electric guitars.

46
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,520
You mean

47
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:01,200
we use folk instruments on stage?

48
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:01,920
Exactly.

49
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:03,880
Let's use the soul of our village

50
00:05:03,880 --> 00:05:05,280
to win this competition.

51
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:06,940
No problem.

52
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:09,050
I'm good at the Sanxian.

53
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:13,360
Qiuqiu,

54
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:14,680
do you

55
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,600
dare to play the wooden drum?

56
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:18,640
I dare.

57
00:05:54,159 --> 00:05:55,960
Don't you want to go check it out?

58
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:57,440
I'm not going.

59
00:05:58,840 --> 00:05:59,840
Wait.

60
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:01,360
Look at this.

61
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:37,600
Why are there more people here than the preliminaries?

62
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:38,240
Qiuqiu,

63
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:40,170
what do you think of my look?

64
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:43,300
You look like a peacock fanning its tail.

65
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:44,690
Well, look at your hair.

66
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:45,960
What about it?

67
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:47,600
You know,

68
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:49,920
we really should get some uniforms.

69
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,240
We're here to make money,

70
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:51,960
not spend it.

71
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:52,960
Why would we get uniforms?

72
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:54,600
Next up is

73
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:55,960
Wildfire Club.

74
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:58,300
Please give them a round of applause.

75
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:00,400
It's our turn.

76
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:01,680
Don't be nervous.

77
00:07:01,960 --> 00:07:02,560
Play well.

78
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:04,120
Stop shaking, okay?

79
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:05,370
Let's huddle up.

80
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:06,040
Come on.

81
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:07,920
Three, two, one.

82
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:09,560
Let's do this!

83
00:07:10,280 --> 00:07:10,840
Bro,

84
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:13,540
we're definitely gonna win this battle.

85
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:15,400
Let's give it our all. Let's move.

86
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:16,240
Let's go.

87
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:41,320
Steady.

88
00:08:44,039 --> 00:08:45,640
The drum isn't making any sound.

89
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:47,040
What do we do?

90
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:48,320
I'm so worried.

91
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:52,360
What's going on?

92
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:54,100
Look at this situation. Yeah.

93
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:54,880
Okay.

94
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:56,440
Yehuo Club,

95
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:58,440
please be ready in three minutes.

96
00:08:58,640 --> 00:09:00,560
Otherwise, you forfeit.

97
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:10,760
Get off the stage.

98
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:18,000
Get down. Get down. Get down.
